groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: Honor Thy Father
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: Traditional 50 Cal Ammo box. Semi-Easy hide for youngsters. Some bushwhacking needed. There is a suggested entrance to the bushes to avoid the most prickers.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description:
An Ammo Can placed just off the Struble trail in an area that my father walks daily. This large cache is Child and Adult friendly with something for everyone. The cache will start with a large collection of toys and other swag. There is a FTF bag for an Adult (over 12) with a Patch, Pin and Cache container. There is FTF bag specifically for a child under age 12, with a hat, patch, pin and small swag. There will be various Travel Bugs starting their journeys here. If you take a GeoCoin or Travel Tag, please log it properly. Special Army National Guard Traveling GeoCoin is one of the Travel Bugs. All Travel Bugs, Log and Pencil are in a Ziploc Bag. Please rehide as well or better.
Congratulations to tjs305 for FTF Adult.
This cache was placed with the permission of Chester County Parks & Recreation Department. All caches must have the permission of Chester County Parks and Recreation Department. Please follow all Chester County Parks and Recreation Rule and Regulations. Parks are open year-round, 8 am to sunset. Dogs are permitted on a 6' leash. Hunting may take place within the parks during applicable hunting seasons. For more information on Chester County Parks and contact information, please visit http://www.chesco.org/ccparks.

groundspeak:log.groundspeak:text: My wife found that sweaters and thorns don't mix well, but she made the find. Found with dawnie22 and 19acassel.
